data.title: Ex-Minister Mahindananda Aluthgamage brought to court
data.byline: Former Minister of Agriculture Mahindananda Aluthgamage, who is currently in remand custody, has been produced before the Colombo Magistrate’s Court by prison officials this morning (May 26).

data.title: Trump says he’ll delay threatened 50% tariff on EU until July
data.byline: President Donald Trump said Sunday that the U.S. will delay implementation of a 50% tariff on goods from the European Union from June 1 until July 9 to buy time for negotiations with the bloc.

data.title: Artists have ability to build cultural bridge between North and South, says President
data.byline: A meeting between President Anura Kumara Disanayake and the Joint Association of Performing Artists of Sri Lanka was held at the Presidential Secretariat, on Sunday (25).

data.title: Special traffic plan around Independence Square due to funeral of Malini Fonseka
data.byline: Vehicular movement will be restricted in and around Independence Square in Colombo, due to the funeral of veteran actress Malini Fonseka scheduled for this evening (26).

data.title: Legal action against 1,470 for maintaining mosquito breeding grounds
data.byline: Over 30,000 premises with potential mosquito breeding sites have been identified during the special island-wide mosquito control program conducted from May 9 to 24, the Ministry of Health said.

data.title: LG Polls: Deadline to submit campaign finance reports ends at midnight tomorrow
data.byline: The deadline for all candidates who contested the 2925 Local Government (LG) Elections to submit their campaign income and expenditure reports ends at midnight tomorrow (27).

data.title: Last rites of Malini Fonseka with state honours today
data.byline: The final rites of Sri Lankan cinema icon and veteran actress Malini Fonseka, widely celebrated as the “Queen of Sri Lankan Cinema,” is scheduled to be performed with full state honours this evening (26) at Independence Square in Colombo.

data.title: Edu Min. launches probe into suicide by student of Wayamba National College of Education
data.byline: The Ministry of Education has launched an urgent investigation into the suicide of a second-year student at the Wayamba National College of Education in Bingiriya.

data.title: New Zealand welcomes Sri Lanka’s application to accede to RCEP agreement
data.byline: Visiting Deputy Prime Minister of New Zealand Winston Peters has welcomed Sri Lanka’s application to accede to the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) agreement.

data.title: Sri Lanka bids farewell to “Queen of Sinhala Cinema,” Malini Fonseka
data.byline: The final rites of Sri Lankan cinema icon and veteran actress Malini Fonseka, widely known as the “Queen of Sri Lankan Cinema,” were performed with full state honours this evening (26 May) at Independence Square in Colombo.

data.title: President meets Lions Clubs Chief to strengthen youth mental health programs
data.byline: President Anura Kumara Dissanayake met with Fabrício Oliveira, International President of Lions Clubs International, at the Presidential Secretariat today (26) to discuss strengthening collaboration on youth mental health and social welfare initiatives in Sri Lanka.

data.title: Funeral ceremony of late Malini Fonseka underway at Independence Square
data.byline: The funeral ceremony of Sri Lankan cinema icon and veteran actress Malini Fonseka, widely known as the “Queen of Sri Lankan Cinema,” has commenced at Independence Square in Colombo.

data.title: Fairly heavy showers in parts of the island today
data.byline: The Department of Meteorology says that  showers or thundershowers will occur at times in Western, Sabaragamuwa and North-western provinces and in Nuwara-Eliya, Kandy, Galle and Matara districts today (26).

data.title: Colombo HC adjourns ‘Sathosa’ case against Johnston Fernando
data.byline: The case filed by the Commission to Investigate Allegations of Bribery or Corruption (CIABOC) against former Minister Johnston Fernando and two others was taken up for hearing once again before the Colombo High Court today (26).

data.title: Police constable suspended following assault incident captured on video
data.byline: A police constable attached to the Gokarella Police Station has been suspended from duties.

data.title: Lilo and Stitch beat Tom Cruise in box office bonanza
data.byline: Disney’s live-action Lilo and Stitch remake and Tom Cruise’s supposedly final Mission: Impossible outing have opened as two of the biggest films of the year in a record-breaking weekend at the box office.

data.title: Remains of veteran actress Malini Fonseka brought to Independence Square
data.byline: The mortal remains of late veteran actress Malini Fonseka has been brought to the Independence Square in Colombo for the general public to pay their last respect.

data.title: Trump says Putin ‘has gone absolutely crazy’ after major Russian attack on Ukraine
data.byline: US President Donald Trump has said that Russian President Vladimir Putin “has gone absolutely CRAZY” and that he is “not happy with what Putin is doing” after Moscow launched its largest aerial attack of its three-year war on Ukraine overnight.

data.title: India overtakes Japan to become the fourth-largest economy: NITI Aayog CEO
data.byline: India overtakes Japan to become the fourth largest economy in the world, Aayog CEO BVR Subrahmanyam has said.

data.title: Special program honoring cinema icon Malini Fonseka live on TV Derana
data.byline: A special program dedicated to veteran actress and Sri Lankan cinema icon Malini Fonseka, fondly known as the “Queen of Sri Lankan Cinema,” is currently being broadcast on TV Derana.

data.title: US first lady says AI is the future of publishing. It’s already happening
data.byline: US first lady Melania Trump released an audiobook version in her voice of her memoir on Thursday — but she won’t actually be the one narrating it.

data.title: India’s Kerala state on alert after ship carrying hazardous cargo capsizes
data.byline: Authorities in India’s southern Kerala state have issued an alert after a ship carrying oil and hazardous cargo leaked and sank off the state’s coast in the Arabian Sea.

data.title: Former Minister Mahindananda granted bail
data.byline: Former Minister of Agriculture Mahindananda Aluthgamage, who was arrested and remanded in connection with the case filed over the importation of a shipment of substandard organic fertiliser from a Chinese company during the previous administration, has been granted bail, Ada Derana reporter said.

data.title: Viral video of assault on foreigner: Police issue clarification and warn against spreading old incidents
data.byline: Sri Lanka Police have issued a clarification regarding a viral video circulating on social media that appears to show a Sri Lankan man assaulting a Filipino national.

data.title: Parliament to debate Personal Data Protection Bill during next session
data.byline: Parliament is scheduled to convene from June 3 (Tuesday) to June 6 (Friday) according to Secretary General of Parliament Kushani Rohanadeera.

data.title: Indian Consulate Officer dies in road accident in Omanthai
data.byline: An officer attached to the Consulate General of India in Jaffna has died following a tragic road accident in Omanthai, Vavuniya this morning (26), according to Omanthai Police.

data.title: Dy Tourism Minister responds to reports of ‘bikini ban’ in Arugam Bay
data.byline: Certain groups are attempting to undermine the tourism industry by spreading false information via social media, Deputy Minister of Tourism Ruwan Chaminda Ranasingha said while clarifying reports of a purported ‘bikini ban in Arugam Bay.

data.title: Mervyn Silva, Prasanna Ranaweera and 3 others further remanded
data.byline: Former Minister Mervyn Silva, former State Minister Prasanna Ranaweera and three others arrested and remanded for allegedly selling a plot of state-owned land in Kiribathgoda to a private party by forging documents, have been further remanded.

data.title: Three arrested with heroin and ICE in Mount Lavinia
data.byline: Three individuals have been arrested for the possession of heroin and crystal methamphetamine (commonly known as ICE) during separate raids conducted in Mount Lavinia, Sri Lanka Police said.

data.title: Supplementary medical professionals warn of trade union action
data.byline: Joint Council for Professions Supplementary to Medicine (JCPSM) has decided to take trade union action due to the government’s failure to provide solutions to issues within its service.

data.title: Russian drones attack Kyiv, other Ukrainian cities, three dead outside the capital
data.byline: Russian forces attacked Kyiv and other cities early on Sunday, injuring at least 11 people in the capital, killing three people in towns around it and damaging dwellings and other buildings, officials said.

data.title: SJB electoral organisers continue to resign
data.byline: A number of electoral organisers of the Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) have resigned from their respective positions due to issues relating to the selection of members for local government bodies.

data.title: New Zealand Deputy PM Winston Peters arrives in Sri Lanka
data.byline: Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs of New Zealand Winston Peters has arrived in the island on an official visit.

data.title: Tourist arrivals in May top 90,000
data.byline: A total of 91,785 tourists have arrived in the country thus far in May, data from the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority (SLTDA) shows.

data.title: 7-year-old killed in wild elephant attack in Gomarankadawala

data.title: Second-year student at Wayamba National College of Education commits suicide in hostel

data.title: Heavy showers above 100mm expected in parts of the island

data.title: Cases of dengue and chikungunya on the rise, Dy Health Minister

data.title: Large crowd gathers to pay last respects to Malini Fonseka

data.title: Only 40 medicinal drugs in short supply at hospitals - Deputy Minister clarifies

data.title: Bird Flu: Several countries halt poultry imports from Brazil
data.byline: India, Albania and Namibia have joined the list of countries imposing a total ban on poultry imports from Brazil, while Angola has opted for a more limited restriction.
